@startuml Sequence Diagram - Semantic Search Flow
!theme cerulean-outline

title SmartMedia - Sequence Diagram (Semantic Search Operation)

participant User as user
participant "SearchBar\n(React)" as searchBar
participant "HomePage\n(React)" as homePage
participant "Zustand Store" as store
participant "Electron Main" as electronMain
participant "Python Backend\n(main.py)" as pyBackend
participant "Sentence\nTransformers" as embedding
participant "FAISS\nIndex" as faiss
participant "SQLite\nDatabase" as database

autonumber

user -> searchBar: Types "sunset beach"
note right of searchBar: User enters search query
activate searchBar

searchBar -> store: updateSearchQuery("sunset beach")
activate store
store -> homePage: Notify listeners
activate homePage
homePage -> searchBar: Disable search button
searchBar -> searchBar: Show loading spinner
deactivate searchBar
deactivate store
deactivate homePage

homePage -> electronMain: IPC("search", "sunset beach")
note right of homePage: Send to Electron main process
activate electronMain

electronMain -> pyBackend: Send JSON command\n{"action": "search", "query": "sunset beach"}
note right of electronMain: ZMQ/stdin communication
activate pyBackend

pyBackend -> embedding: encode("sunset beach")
note right of pyBackend: Generate query embedding
activate embedding
embedding --> pyBackend: vector[1536] (float32)
deactivate embedding

note over pyBackend: Load FAISS index\n(if not already loaded)
pyBackend -> faiss: search(query_vector, k=50)
note right of faiss: Find k nearest neighbors
activate faiss
faiss -> faiss: Compute cosine similarity
faiss -> faiss: Return top 50 results
faiss --> pyBackend: [(id, similarity_score), ...]
deactivate faiss

pyBackend -> database: SELECT * FROM images WHERE id IN (result_ids)
note right of pyBackend: Fetch full metadata\nfor top results
activate database
database --> pyBackend: [ImageMetadata...] (50 rows)
deactivate database

pyBackend -> pyBackend: Rank results by similarity + recency
note right of pyBackend: Sort by:\n1. Similarity score\n2. Date modified (newer first)

pyBackend --> electronMain: JSON result\n{"results": [...]}
note right of pyBackend: ~45 total results found
deactivate pyBackend

electronMain -> electronMain: Parse JSON results
electronMain --> homePage: IPC return\n{results: [...], total: 45}
deactivate electronMain

homePage -> store: updateSearchResults([...])
note right of homePage: Update app state
activate store
store -> homePage: Notify listeners\n(Re-render gallery)
deactivate store

homePage -> homePage: Filter gallery by results
note right of homePage: Show only matching images\nin grid layout

searchBar -> searchBar: Hide loading spinner
searchBar -> searchBar: Enable search button

user -> homePage: Clicks on image
note right of user: User selects result
activate homePage
homePage -> store: setSelectedImage(image)
activate store
store --> homePage: Open PhotoViewer
deactivate store
deactivate homePage

homePage -> user: Display full image viewer
note right of homePage: Show caption, metadata,\nAI tags

user -> searchBar: Clear search
note right of user: Or type new query
searchBar -> store: clearSearch()
activate store
store -> homePage: Show all images
deactivate store

---

partition "Performance Notes" {
  note right of pyBackend
    **Search Timeline:**
    • embed query: ~50ms
    • load FAISS: ~100ms (cached after first)
    • FAISS search: ~20ms (50 neighbors)
    • DB fetch: ~30ms (50 rows)
    • Ranking: ~5ms
    • Total: ~205ms (subsequent searches ~105ms)
    
    **Optimization:**
    ✓ FAISS cached in RAM
    ✓ Index pre-computed at scan time
    ✓ Parallel queries possible
    ✓ Results paginated
  end note
}

---

partition "Error Handling" {
  alt Search Failed
    pyBackend ->> electronMain: {"success": false, "error": "..."}
    electronMain ->> homePage: IPC return with error
    homePage ->> user: Display error message
  else FAISS not loaded
    pyBackend ->> pyBackend: Generate index from DB embeddings
    note right: First search takes longer
    pyBackend ->> faiss: Index generated
  else Empty Results
    pyBackend --> electronMain: {"results": [], "total": 0}
    electronMain --> homePage: Empty results
    homePage --> user: "No matches found"
  end
}

note bottom
  **Search Flow Summary:**
  1. User types in SearchBar
  2. React state updated via Zustand
  3. IPC message sent to Electron
  4. Python vectorizes query (Sentence-Transformers)
  5. FAISS similarity search (fast, GPU-optimized)
  6. SQL fetch full metadata for results
  7. Results ranked and returned
  8. UI re-renders gallery filtered to results
  9. User can click to view, share, or tag
  
  **Key Features:**
  • Semantic (meaning-based) not keyword-based
  • Fast: <200ms end-to-end
  • Accurate: pre-computed embeddings
  • Scalable: FAISS is production-grade
end note

@enduml
